review_blob: Can from Lawson into a glass. Great color. Head faded quickly though. Decent malt giving medium mouthfeel. Some hop bitterness and flavor, not so much aroma though. Better than most of the "special" Yebisu they are constantly producing.

The name is an oxymoron. Amber lager? Regardless it pours a white head and is pale in color. A beer in search of a style is my guess. Lager-like, but unlike any you have had. No need to pay a premium for this one.
beer_name: Suntory Craftmans Beer Vol. 6 Senretsu no Kaori Amber Lager

review_blob: Not undrinkable, but hardly a great wheat beer. Low head, pale in color. Beware of mistreated bottles in Bali (hot shelves).
Horrible beer. Possibly infected, or possibly mistreated. In any case, give it a miss in Bali, even if you are desperate for something other than lager. Big waste of money.
Considering I like Guinness, this was pretty disappointing. Bit sour, and at 4.9% pretty low alcohol.
